  "response": "In South India, several agricultural practices are considered profitable. Some of the most profitable types of farming include:\n\n1. Coconut Farming\n- High demand\n- Good export potential\n- Low maintenance\n- Steady income\n- Suitable in Kerala, Tamil Nadu, and coastal regions\n\n2. Coffee Plantation\n- High-value crop\n- Good export market\n- Primarily in Karnataka and Kerala\n- Arabica and Robusta varieties\n\n3. Banana Cultivation\n- Quick returns\n- Multiple harvests per year\n- High market demand\n- Suitable in Tamil Nadu and Karnataka\n\n4. Sugarcane Farming\n- High-value crop\n- Government support\n- Good market rates\n- Suitable in Maharashtra and Karnataka\n\n5. Spice Cultivation\n- Pepper\n- Cardamom\n- Turmeric\n- High export potential\n- Good profit margins\n\n6. Floriculture\n- Rose\n- Jasmine\n- Marigold\n- Export potential\n- Low land requirement\n\n7. Dairy Farming\n- Consistent income\n- Low initial investment\n- Good market demand\n- Suitable across South India\n\nThe profitability depends on factors like land quality, climate, market demand, and farming techniques.",
